import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='lon', y='lat', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude across all capital cities?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    capital_cities = data.groupby('state').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    capital_cities = capital_cities.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    ax = sns.barplot(x='state', y='counts', data=capital_cities, palette='Blues_d')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    ax.axhline(y=capital_cities['counts'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max number of capital cities: {:.2f}'.format(capital_cities['counts'].max()))
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x="lon", y="lat", data=data, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['lon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean Longitude: {data['lon'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axhline(y=data['lat'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean Latitude: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title("What is the average longitude and latitude of all capital cities?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='lon', y='lat', hue='state', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude within each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=2, borderaxespad=0.)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.regplot(x="lon", y="lat", data=data, scatter_kws={"s": 50}, line_kws={"color": "red"})
    ax.set(xlabel='Longitude', ylabel='Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between longitude and latitude of capital cities?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
